body:
Were you having the same issue as issue #11? If so, downloading the most recent version from here might resolve the issue.

The only problem I an see with changing the code to be:
```
Dictionary<int, string> end_state = TrackChanges.Command.GetSnapshot(a);
_start_state = TrackChanges.Command.GetSnapshot(a);
string results = TrackChanges.Command.ReportDifferences(doc, _start_state, end_state);
```

instead of:

```
Dictionary<int, string> end_state = TrackChanges.Command.GetSnapshot(a);
string results = TrackChanges.Command.ReportDifferences(doc, _start_state, end_state);
_start_state = TrackChanges.Command.GetSnapshot(a);
```

would be that the start and end states would be the same when the ReportDifferences function is called, so it would never report any pinned or unpinned items. Let me know if I misread your code though or if the issue still persists with the latest version.
